# AhaDiff

Use AhaDiff after code changes to capture verified lessons, claims, quiz cards,
scores, and run artifacts for the current diff.

- Run `ahadiff learn HEAD~1..HEAD` for the latest commit.
- Run `ahadiff learn --staged` before committing staged work.
- Run `ahadiff quiz <run_id>` for generated recall and transfer questions.
- Run `ahadiff review` to revisit due SRS cards.
- Run `ahadiff verify <run_id>` before trusting generated artifacts.
- Run `ahadiff improve --rounds 1` for one targeted improvement round.
- Run `ahadiff serve` to inspect local run artifacts in the WebUI.

Additional learn capture modes: `ahadiff learn --last`, `ahadiff learn --since
"2 hours ago"`, `ahadiff learn --unstaged`, and `ahadiff learn --patch FILE|-`.

## Boundaries

- Keep provider credentials in environment variables.
- Do not commit `.ahadiff/audit.private.jsonl`.
- Treat `.ahadiff/` as local state.
- Prefer verified claims with file-line evidence.
- Do not upload `.ahadiff/` artifacts to external services without explicit user consent.
